                {
                    "analysis": "This is a ransomware sample. It enumerates local and network drives to find and encrypt user files using the Windows CryptoAPI (`CryptEncrypt`). It avoids execution on Russian-language systems by checking the system language ID (0x19). After encryption, it drops ransom notes and changes the desktop wallpaper to a bitmap named `WallpapeR.bmp` which is created in a directory named 'Rondo'. The malware attempts to contact C2 servers, including `fkksjobnn43[.]org` and a Tor domain `rktazuzi7hbln7sy[.]onion`. Finally, it deletes its original executable using the command `cmd.exe /C del /Q /F` to clean up its tracks.",
